/// Sigmoid MoE Router (DeepSeek-V3 style)
///
/// MoE routing with sigmoid scoring + auxiliary-loss-free token-choice
/// (noaux_tc) load balancing — DeepSeek-V3's approach.
///
/// Instead of softmax + auxiliary loss, uses:
/// 1. Sigmoid scores for expert gating (allows multi-hot selection)
/// 2. Token-choice load balancing via bias adjustment (no aux loss needed)
/// 3. Top-k selection per token based on sigmoid scores
///
/// Parameters:
/// - dim: Input/output feature dimension
/// - num_experts: Total number of expert networks
/// - active_experts: Number of experts activated per token (top-k)
/// - expert_dim: Hidden dimension within each expert FFN
///
/// Shape Contract:
/// - Input: [batch, seq, dim]
/// - Output: [batch, seq, dim]
///
/// Reference: DeepSeek-V3 Technical Report (2024)
/// "Auxiliary-Loss-Free Load Balancing Strategy for Mixture-of-Experts"
neuron SigmoidMoERouter(dim, num_experts, active_experts, expert_dim):
    in: [batch, seq, dim]
    out: [batch, seq, dim]
    impl: neuroscript,routing/SigmoidMoERouter
